node.title: Livestream: Mahuta with update on Tonga, Hipkins on MIQ room release delay
node.description: The Foreign Affairs Minister, Defence Minister and COVID-19 Response Minister speak in New Plymouth.
node.content: ["This livestream is expected to start at 2:40pm.\u00a0", "Foreign Affairs Minister Nanaia Mahuta will be joined by Defence Minister Peeni Henare at Labour's caucus retreat at New Plymouth to provide an update on the Government's response to the eruption and tsunami that has devastated Tonga.\u00a0", "COVID-19 Response Minister Chris Hipkins will then hold a press conference to answer questions about the Government's postponement of the release of managed isolation and quarantine (MIQ) rooms due to Omicron.\u00a0", "Watch the livestream.\u00a0", "App users watch here."]
